China March Trade Deficit With BRICS Increases 50.5%

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-15T03:44:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/china-march-trade-deficit-with-brics-increases-50-5-correct-.html
(Corrects export figure in second paragraph.)  China ’s trade deficit with the
other members of the BRICS grouping grew 50.5 percent in March
from a year earlier to $2 billion, the customs bureau said in a
statement on its website today.  Total exports from China to Brazil, India, Russia and  South
Africa  rose 48.5 percent last month to $9.93 billion while
imports gained 48.8 percent to $11.93 billion, the bureau said.  In the first quarter, China’s trade deficit with the other
BRICS nations widened to $6.19 billion, 5.5 times more than the
same period last year, the bureau said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nerys Avery at 
 navery2@bloomberg.net  